section_text: 88 1 The enactments specified in Schedule 1 to this Act shall have effect subject to the amendments there specified, being amendments consequential on the provisions of this Act. 2 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .  6 The foregoing provisions of this section are without prejudice to  sections 16(1) and 17(2)( a ) of the  Interpretation Act 1978  (effect of repeals).

90 1 This Act may be cited as the Insurance Companies Act 1974. 2 Subject to section 89 above, this Act shall come into operation at the expiration of the period of one month beginning with the date on which it is passed. 3 This Act shall . . .   extend to Northern Ireland.
